# Codex Reviewer Findings — ПССК Prompt Quality Review
Chain: pssk-cv-b2-v2-260416-164933-8b6e

## Issues Found
1. [CRITICAL] Unix shell examples are not compatible with the actual runner — The prompt uses `cp`, `wc -l`, bare `grep`, and piped grep checks in Preparation/FROZEN verification, but this chain runs on Windows PowerShell unless Bash is explicitly requested. That can fail before implementation starts, and the later verification block repeats the same problem. PROMPT FIX: Replace shell snippets with tool-agnostic instructions or explicitly require the Bash tool for every command block and provide Windows-safe alternatives.

2. [CRITICAL] Fix 3 leaves the terminal trigger unresolved and violates the frozen persistence contract — The prompt literally says the reviewer must determine the right closed-status field, then proposes `currentTable?.status === 'closed' || 'completed'` plus localStorage key `cv_terminal_dismissed`. That is not enough for an implementation prompt, and it conflicts with frozen R4 wording about durable persist `terminalStateShownForVersion`. A table-id-only dismissal can suppress the terminal for later sessions on the same table. PROMPT FIX: Name the exact close signal from the real data model and require versioned persistence keyed by the table/session version, not only `currentTable.id`.

3. [CRITICAL] Fix 2 targets the wrong render structure for buckets — In the real file, `statusBuckets` is defined around `~456`, `currentGroupKeys` around `~469`, and the UI later renders buckets through a generic mapped section with `bucketOrder = ['served', 'in_progress']` and `bucketDisplayNames[key]`. The prompt tells the implementer to patch `groupLabels` and “add pending after `statusBuckets.in_progress` render”, but that is not the real control point, so pending can be added incompletely or not show at all. PROMPT FIX: Instruct updates at all actual sites: `statusBuckets`, `currentGroupKeys`, the served auto-collapse logic, the mapped bucket order/render list, and the bucket display-name source actually used by the section.

4. [MEDIUM] The prompt bypasses existing status normalization and overuses raw `o.status` checks — The current component already normalizes statuses through `getOrderStatus(o)` and `stageInfo.internal_code`; for example, cancelled filtering in `todayMyOrders` uses `stageInfo?.internal_code === 'cancel'` with raw fallback. Fix 1 and Fix 2 snippets revert to raw checks like `o.status !== 'cancelled'` and `o.status === 'submitted'`, which can miscount totals and mis-bucket orders when stage info exists. PROMPT FIX: Require reusing `getOrderStatus(o)` as the primary source for served/cancelled/pending decisions, with raw `o.status` only as a fallback.

5. [MEDIUM] Scope lock conflicts with the mandatory i18n-dictionary instruction — The prompt says “Only `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx`” and then later says the batch is required to add new keys to the i18n dictionary. In the real file, `tr(key, fallback)` already provides safe fallbacks, so forcing a dictionary edit is not necessary for a safe scoped change and may push the executor into unauthorized edits outside scope. PROMPT FIX: Either expand scope and name the exact i18n file to edit, or remove the dictionary requirement and explicitly rely on `tr(..., fallback)` in this batch.

6. [MEDIUM] Fix 4’s sample self-block does not match the real table-row pattern and weakens the pending badge spec — The real table section renders dish rows like `dish_name × quantity` or an order-total fallback when `items.length === 0`. The sample self-block instead compresses each order to “N блюд” and shows only an icon-only pending mark, while R1 requires text+icon `⏳ Ожидает` in the table tab. That sample is likely to be copied literally and produce inconsistent UI. PROMPT FIX: Tell the implementer to reuse the existing `guestOrders.map(...)` row renderer unchanged for the self-block and only change the surrounding card/header; for pending, reuse the full badge text.

7. [LOW] Several line anchors are stale enough to slow execution — Verified anchors in the current file do not match the prompt’s references: `pluralizeRu` is around `~294`, `statusBuckets` around `~456`, `submittedTableTotal` around `~525`, and `showTableOrdersSection` around `~542`, while some prompt references place related items much later. The instructions remain partly usable, but they will force unnecessary searching and reduce executor confidence. PROMPT FIX: Refresh line numbers against the exact target revision, or switch to identifier-based anchors only.

